Gdańsk University of Technology
The Gdańsk University of Technology is a higher education institution located in Gdańsk, Poland. It has a well-defined structure, comprising various faculties and departments that offer a range of courses and programs to its students. The institution is governed by a rector, dean, and student government, each with specific roles and responsibilities.

The Gdańsk University of Technology oversees various aspects of student life, including recruitment, transfer, and confirmation of learning outcomes. It provides academic programs and services to students, adhering to its own rules and regulations, which govern student registration and diploma awarding procedures. The institution also defines the rules for studies and student rights, ensuring a structured and organized educational environment.

The university's academic programs and services are designed to cater to the needs of its students, providing them with a comprehensive educational experience. Its rules and regulations for diploma theses are also in place to ensure the quality and integrity of the academic work produced by students. The institution's student government and study programs are governed by the university, indicating its direct involvement in student affairs.

Overall, the Gdańsk University of Technology is a comprehensive higher education institution that provides a structured and organized educational environment, governed by a clear set of rules and regulations, and dedicated to the academic growth and development of its students.

Rector
The Rector is the authorized person making decisions on student removal and reinstatement.<SEP>The Rector is the head of the university and makes decisions regarding scholarships and regulations.<SEP>The Rector is the superior of all university students, overseeing various aspects of student life.<SEP>The rector is the head of the university and responsible for making decisions regarding studies.

Dean
The Dean is the head of the academic faculty, responsible for academic decisions and regulations, as well as overseeing student registration and reinstatement. They are responsible for managing the examination process, making decisions, and administrative tasks within the faculty. This includes overseeing student affairs, including academic matters and disciplinary proceedings, and is also responsible for diploma procedures. As the head of the faculty, the Dean is responsible for making decisions regarding student applications and regulations, as well as study programs. They serve as the superior of all students at a given faculty, responsible for specific aspects of student life, and are ultimately responsible for the overall management and direction of the faculty.

Student Government
